  "description": [
    "Para Villa Residents File Suit Against Zoning Para Villa Heights residents living in the Drivein Theatre area went to court nearly 100 per cent strong this week to prevent the county from rezoning their property for a multiple housing project The area was selected as a ten tative site for a low cost public housing project after hearings be fore a special slum clearance com mittee the county planning board VOL XXVIII NO 48 PRICE TEN CENTS MYSTERY SURROUNDS SLAYING OF WHITE DR LIVE OAK lnsiders in this quiet college town insist that the whole story has not been told in the pistol slaying of a popular White doctor by the wife of the richest Negro in town Attractive Mrs Ruby McCol lum 37 and the mother of three children is being held in the state prison at Raiford for safe keep ing after white residents became incensed over the killing of the 42yearold physician The dead man Dr C Leroy Adams was a state senate nominee Sam McCollum husband of the slayer died from a heart attack Monday morning after fleeing to Ocala from Live Oak after he was warned to leave town for his own good State troopers"
